Part 1: Directions on getting started and using Git, Webstorm and Github

 1. Setting up Git
  
  1. Downloading and Installing Git: 
  Step 1: Head to Git's official website: https://git-scm.com/downloads
  Step 2: Install the appropriate verison for your computer
  Step 3: Follow the list of instructions provided on the site

 2. Configuring Git:
  Step 4: Open a command prompt
  Step 5: Create your username and email address that you want associated with your account using the below prompt of code (lines 12 and 13)
  git config --global user.name "Your Name"
  git config --global user.email "your_email@example.com"

  2. Setting up Github
    
1. Signing up for GitHub:
  Step 1: Go to GitHub's official website: https://github.com/
  Step 2: Sign up for an account on the site if you don't already have one
  Step 3: Once you're logged in, click on the "+" icon in the top right corner and select "New Repository"
  Step 4: With that "New Repository", fill in the repository name, description, and alter any more additional settings if needed
  Step 5: Click "Create Repository" to official create your new repository

  3. Cloning the Repository in WebStorm:
    
1. Opening WebStorm:
   Step 1: Launch WebStorm IDE on your computer.
     
2. Clone Repository:
Step 1: Go to "VCS" > "Get from Version Control" > "Git"
Step 2: Paste the URL of your GitHub repository in the "URL" field
Step 3: Select the directory where you want to clone the repository
Step 4: Click "Clone" to clone the repository to your local machine

  4. Making Changes and Committing:

1. Open Project:
Step 1: Open the cloned project in WebStorm.
  
2. Make Changes:
Step 1: Modify files in your project as needed.
  
3. Commit Changes:
Step 1: Go to "VCS" > "Commit" or press Ctrl + K.
Step 2: Select the files you want to commit.
Step 3: Write a commit message describing your changes.
Step 4: Click "Commit" to save the changes to your local repository.

5. Pushing Changes to GitHub:

1. Push Changes:
Step 1: After committing changes, go to "VCS" > "Git" > "Push".
Step 2: If prompted, enter your GitHub username and password.
Step 3: Click "OK" to push your changes to the remote repository on GitHub.

6. Pulling Changes from GitHub:

1. Pull Changes:
Step 1: To fetch and merge changes made by others, go to "VCS" > "Git" > "Pull".
Step 2: Select the branch you want to pull changes from.
Step 3: Click "Pull" to update your local repository with the changes from GitHub.

7. Branching and Merging:

1.Creating a New Branch:
Step 1: Go to "VCS" > "Git" > "Branches" > "New Branch".
Step 2: Enter a name for your new branch and click "Create".

2. Switching Branches:
Step 1: To switch between branches, go to "VCS" > "Git" > "Branches" and select the desired branch.

3. Merging Branches:
Step 1: Go to "VCS" > "Git" > "Merge Changes".
Step 2: Select the branch you want to merge into the current branch.
Step 3: Resolve any merge conflicts if necessary and commit the merge.
  
